<TITLE>Paul Merson What Arsenal problem is weighing on Arsene Wenger s mind</TITLE>
<TEXT>
Paul Merson has suggested that Arsene Wenger s touchline antics were a result of the uncertainty surrounding Mesut Ozil and Alexis Sanchez s futures at Arsenal Wenger has received a four game touchline suspension after the Frenchman pushed a fourth official during Arsenal s tense 2 1 win against Burnley at the Emirates Stadium last weekend Both Ozil and Sanchez are still in negotiations with the north London club about new contracts amid growing uncertainty surrounding whether Wenger s key men will stay at Arsenal Arsenal are in second place in the Premier League and eight points behind Chelsea but Wenger will now be absent from the touchline when the Gunners take on the Premier League leaders at Stamford Bridge next weekend Speaking to Daily Star about Wenger s behaviour last weekend Merson said You can t do what Wenger did It s out of order But I think the situation with Alexis Sanchez and Mesut Ozil is playing on his mind as well It s been going on for weeks now and it s taking it s toll It should have been done by now but I think both players are waiting to see what happens Ozil moved to Arsenal in a 42 5m deal from La Liga outfit Real Madrid in the 2013 summer transfer window Sanchez completed a 35m switch to Arsenal from Barcelona less than 12 months after Ozil s move Get 5 1 enhanced odds on Man United to beat Wigan in the FA Cup on Sunday Click here to sign up for an account now Note enhanced winnings are credited in free bets T C s apply MORE Latest transfer news and gossip MORE Back to The Sport Review homepage MORE Man United latest news MORE Arsenal latest news MORE Chelsea latest news MORE Liverpool latest news
